<tbody><tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Wireless Personal Area Network (WPAN)</td><td bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Within reach of an individual</td><td bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Alternative or replacement to cables for peripherals</td><td bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Bluetooth, ZigBee, NFC</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Wireless Local Area Network (WLAN)</td><td bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Within a building or campus</td><td bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Wireless extension of wired network</td><td bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">IEEE 802.11 (Wi-Fi)</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Wireless ad hoc network (Also referred to as a wireless mesh network or mobile ad hoc network or MANET)</td><td bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Typically 100m which can be extended by multihop communication of nodes</td><td bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Variety of applications where central nodes can't be relied upon, i.e. field operations, surveillance networks, home, and street lighting networks</td><td bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Not restricted to any one technology or protocol</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Wireless Metropolitan Area Network (Wireless MAN)</td><td bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Citywide</td><td bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Allows several WLANs to interconnect to cover a metropolitan area and provide a connection to a WAN</td><td bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">IEEE 802.16 (WiMAX)</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Wireless Wide Area Network (Wireless WAN or WWAN)</td><td bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Regional, national, or global</td><td bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">Typically delivered to smartphones and other handheld devices</td><td bgcolor="#FBEOC9" style="color: black;">GSM/UMTS, CDMA One/CDMA2000 and WiMAX</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Cellular network</td><td bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Regional, national, or global</td><td bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Voice and data cellular networks</td><td bgcolor="#C2D4FF" style="color: black;">Cellular (UMTS, LTE, OG-5G, etc.)</td></tr>
